lse,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: We went out with the Messenger of Allah, peace and blessings be upon him, from Medina to Mecca and he would pray two cycles\u00a0at a time until he returned. Yahya ibn Abi Ishaq said, \u201cHow long did he remain in Mecca?\u201d Anas said, \u201cTen days.\u201d Source:\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":25503,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2017\/12\/01\/bismillah-begin-salat\/","url_meta":{"origin":25655,"position":1},"title":"Hadith on Bismillah: Reciting name of Allah to begin prayer","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"December 1, 2017","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, as well as Abu Bakr and Umar, may Allah be pleased with them, would open the prayer by reciting, \u201cAll praise is due to Allah.\u201d (1:1) In the narration of Muslim, Anas said: I did not hear any of them\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":17037,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2013\/11\/25\/sajdah-salat-not-like-kalb\/","url_meta":{"origin":25655,"position":2},"title":"Hadith on Sujud: Keep forearms raised in prostration","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"November 25, 2013","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cBe straight in prostration and let none of you put his forearms on the ground like a dog.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 788, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 Muslim 493 Grade: Muttafaqun Alayhi (authenticity agreed upon) according to Al-Bukhari and Muslim \u0639\u064e\u0646\u0652\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19348,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/06\/17\/prophet-lightens-salat-for-child\/","url_meta":{"origin":25655,"position":3},"title":"Hadith on Ease: The Prophet lightens prayer on occasion","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"June 17, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said, \u201cVerily, I might\u00a0begin the prayer and I intend to prolong it, but then I hear the crying of an infant. I will\u00a0shorten the prayer as\u00a0I know his crying will distress his mother.\u201d Source: S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323 al-Bukha\u0304ri\u0304 710, S\u0323ah\u0323i\u0304h\u0323\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Wisdom \u0627\u0644\u062d\u0643\u0645\u0629","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/wisdom-al-hikmah\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":33062,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2019\/08\/03\/how-bilal-got-into-jannah\/","url_meta":{"origin":25655,"position":4},"title":"Hadith on Sahaba: How Bilal ibn Rabah got into Paradise","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"August 3, 2019","format":false,"excerpt":"Abu Huraira reported: The Prophet, peace and blessings be upon him, said to Bilal at the time of dawn prayer, \u201cO Bilal, tell me of the most hopeful deed you practiced in Islam.\u00a0 I heard the scuffle of your sandals before me in Paradise.\u201d Bilal said, \u201cThe most hopeful deed\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Righteousness \u0627\u0644\u0628\u0631","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/righteousness-al-birr\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]},{"id":19909,"url":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/2014\/10\/02\/anas-do-not-pray-to-graves\/","url_meta":{"origin":25655,"position":5},"title":"Hadith on Graves: O Anas, do not pray towards the graves","author":"Abu Amina Elias","date":"October 2, 2014","format":false,"excerpt":"Anas ibn Malik reported: Umar ibn al-Khattab, may Allah be pleased with him, saw me while I was praying near a grave and he raised his voice, saying, \u201cThe grave!\u201d I thought he said something else, so I looked toward the sky. Umar came and he said, \u201cIndeed, I said\u2026","rel":"","context":"In &quot;Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645&quot;","block_context":{"text":"Sin \u0627\u0644\u0625\u062b\u0645","link":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/category\/sin-al-ithm\/"},"img":{"alt_text":"","src":"","width":0,"height":0},"classes":[]}],"_links":{"self":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25655","targetHints":{"allow":["GET"]}}],"collection":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts"}],"about":[{"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/types\/post"}],"author":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/users\/3712"}],"replies":[{"embeddable":true,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/comments?post=25655"}],"version-history":[{"count":0,"href":"https:\/\/www.abuaminaelias.com\/dailyhadithonline\/wp-json\/wp\/v2\/posts\/25655\/revisions"}],"wp:att